PdCl$_{2}$ is known to exist in four different structures at ambient pressure (Evers, 2010): \begin{itemize} \item \href{current_web_home_dir/A2B_oP6_58_g_a-001}{orthorhombic $\alpha$-PdCl$_{2}$}, \item \href{current_web_home_dir/A2B_hR18_148_2f_f-001}{rhombohedral $\beta$-PdCl$_{2}$}, \item \href{current_web_home_dir/A2B_mP6_14_e_a-001}{monoclinic $\gamma$-PdCl$_{2}$}  (this structure), and \item \href{current_web_home_dir/A2B_mP6_10_mn_bc-001}{monoclinic $\delta$-PdCl$_{2}$}. \end{itemize} ~ \vspace{-.25in} 
 (Evers, 2010) place the palladium atoms on the (2c) Wyckoff position. We have shifted the origin so that the palladium atoms are at the (2a) position. 
 Data was taken at 300K.
